duced to be illusions.\n&gt;\n&gt;For example, let me as=\r\nsume that &quot;I, Narasimha Rao, an individual being \n&gt;in this world&quot; is not an=\r\n illusion and a valid and true entity. I can \n&gt;first accept it to be real a=\r\nnd then start analyzing various extensions \n&gt;of that entity. For example, p=\r\neople&#39;s views on this entity are formed \n&gt;based on an impression/reflection=\r\n of this entity in their minds, which \n&gt;is influenced by this entity to som=\r\ne extent, but not fully. Just as my \n&gt;reflection in different mirrors may l=\r\nook different based on the colors, \n&gt;dust, refractive properties etc of the=\r\n mirrors etc, my reflection in \n&gt;different minds may be different. Just as =\r\nI cannot think that my \n&gt;reflections in all mirrors around me are extension=\r\ns of myself and start \n&gt;celebrating or ruing anything happeneing to those r=\r\neflections, so should \n&gt;I not think that my reflections in the minds of peo=\r\nple around me are \n&gt;extensions of myself and start celebrating or ruing any=\r\nthing happening \n&gt;to those reflections!\n&gt;\n&gt;Thus, I can reject a lot of noti=\r\nons that I may tend to hang on to, as an \n&gt;illusion. This is what I am sayi=\r\nng above. I may not be an illusion, a \n&gt;mirror (mind of someone) may not be=\r\n an illusion, my image in the mirror \n&gt;(that person&#39;s notion of who I am) m=\r\nay not be an illusion, BUT my \n&gt;thinking that my image in the mirror is an =\r\nextension of my personality \n&gt;is an illusion.\n&gt;\n&gt;Similarly, we build compli=\r\ncated structures in our own minds regarding \n&gt;various external objects our =\r\nsenses perceive. When senses perceive those \n&gt;objects, mind thinks of a not=\r\nional being that is far more complicated \n&gt;than the objective reality repre=\r\nsented by it! It is influenced by many \n&gt;notions arising in our conditionin=\r\ng and not just based on the concrete \n&gt;objective reality. Again, such notio=\r\nns can be identified and rejected as \n&gt;illusions.\n&gt;\n&gt;As you identify and re=\r\nject each layer of obvious illusion about your \n&gt;sense of who you are, who/=\r\nwhat you are dealing with, you eventually \n&gt;realize unconditioned Self. Unt=\r\nil then, &quot;jaganmithya&quot; is a meaningless \n&gt;and also perhaps a dangerous noti=\r\non.\n&gt;\n&gt;Best regards,\n&gt;Narasimha\n&gt;------------------------------------------=\r\n----------------\n&gt;Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writ=\r\nings,\n&gt;&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:\n&gt;=\r\nhttp://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n&gt;Films that make a difference: http://Sarasw=\r\natiFilms.org\n&gt;Spirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\n&gt;Jyo=\r\ntish writings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings\n&gt;Twitter ID: @=\r\nhomam108\n&gt;----------------------------------------------------------\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt; D=\r\near Narasimha,\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt; Jagat isnt mithya. Brahman is satya & jagat 2 is saty=\r\na.\n&gt;&gt;&gt; Neither mirror nor ur image in it r &quot;illusions&quot;. They r &quot;real&quot;. But =\r\n\n&gt;&gt;&gt; ur thinking 1/2\n&gt;&gt;&gt; that ur image in mirror is ur extension is an illu=\r\nsion.\n&gt;&gt;&gt; Excitement/sadness abt things happenin 2 d mirror image is an \n&gt;&gt;=\r\n&gt; illusion.2/2\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; Can you please clarify the concept of satya & non-m=\r\nithya in light of\n&gt;&gt; Vasishtha&#39;s words in Yoga Vasishtha (2.3.11 - 2.3.18)?=\r\n\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; There is a chain starting from some examples which are obviously\n&gt;&gt; =\r\nmithya (=E0=A4=A8=E0=A5=8C=E0=A4=B8=E0=A5=8D=E0=A4=AA=E0=A4=A8=E0=A5=8D=E0=\r\n=A4=A6=E0=A4=A4=E0=A4=B0=E0=A5=81=E0=A4=AF=E0=A4=BE=E0=A4=A8=E0=A4=B5=E0=A4=\r\n=A4=E0=A5=8D etc), which is the basis of the world (=E0=A4=A4=E0=A4=A6=E0=\r\n=A5=87=E0=A4=B5\n&gt;&gt; ... =E0=A4=9C=E0=A5=80=E0=A